# Workstream Coding Rules

## Python
- Use Python 3.12+ features and type hints
- All async I/O with httpx and aiosqlite
- Follow ruff and black formatting
- Keep functions under 50 lines
- Use logging module, not print()

## FastAPI
- All routes in app.py with section comment headers
- Return JSONResponse for API endpoints
- Use Request for body parsing

## Frontend
- All UI in static/index.html
- Vanilla JS, no frameworks
- CSS variables for theming (--accent, --surface, etc.)
- Tab-based navigation via switchTab()

## Git
- Conventional commits: feat:, fix:, docs:, chore:, test:
- Branch naming: feat/, fix/, docs/ prefixes
